textBeforeTable: Good luck to New Mexico this weekend. We'd love to see another Championship picture featuring Rush players next Monday! In other games from the weekend featuring former Rush players, the New Mexico men advanced to the Men's College Cup with a 1-0 win over Washington. New Mexico has yet to give up a goal in the tournament and will take on Notre Dame in the Semi-finals Friday. Four Rush alumni play for the Lobos. In the D3 final four, Texas Rush alum Kirsten Bevan and Trinity University beat Middlebury 2-1 to advance to the Championship before falling 2-0 to William Smith.  Congratulations ladies! A story book season for the UCLA Bruins has ended with the team winning the programs first ever National Championship in Women's soccer! Gabbi Miranda, Darian Jenkins and the Bruins knocked off the overall No. 1 seed Florida State Seminoles 1-0 in overtime of the Women's College Cup on Sunday. The Bruins beat three No.1 seeds in winning the title (North Carolina, Virginia, Florida State) the 110th overall National Championship for UCLA, tops in the country. Game details available here. 12.09.13 - UCLA are National Champions! textAfterTable: 12.02.13 - Rush players advance to Women's College Cup, Men's Teams into Elite 8 The NCAA Tournament has reached December and that means it is time for the College Cup! Rush alumni are still playing in both the Women's Division I and III tournaments and the Men's Division I tournament will send at least one Rush alum to the College Cup as Washington and New Mexico face off in the Elite Eight. Kelsey Loupee and Virginia Tech will host take on No. 1 seed Florida State in semi-final 1 on Friday Dec. 6 followed by Gabbi Miranda and Darian Jenkins taking on Virginia after knocking off the last two NCAA Champions the past two weeks (North Carolina and Stanford). Texas Rush alum Kirsten Bevan and Trinity University host Middlebury on Friday December 6 as they seek a trip to the National Championship game. Good luck to all Rush players in this weeks games!
